The traditional odometer positioning method has high accuracy and good stability for a short
duration and short distance. However, for a long duration and long distance, it cannot accurately
reflect the coordinates of the delivery robot. The improved odometer positioning method based on
the IMU is less stable than the traditional odometer positioning method, but it can reflect the
coordinates of the delivery robot accurately over a long duration and long distance.
